cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new module to replace dilated convolutions in the backbone, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning models. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions experiments and results, which could make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
